Overall Description¶

Developed a script in Python that can scrape a provided URL and its subsequent hyperlinks for words that appear most frequently
Utilized the html.parser module as a template for defining classes and methods that can collect successive webpages and their relevant content for arrangementm

#web crawler that ignores visited sites
visited = set() #initialize visited to an empty set
total = []

def crawl2(url):
    """a recursive web crawler that calls analyze()
    on every visited web page"""
    
    #add url to set of visited pages
    global visited #warns the programmer
    visited.add(url)
    
    #analyze() returns a list of hyperlink URLs in web page url
    links, stuff = analyze(url)
    
    #combine the content of each URL into one super list
    global total
    total += stuff
    
    #recusrively continue crawl from every link in links
    for link in links:
        #follow link only if not visited
        if link not in visited and link[:len(url)] == url:
            try:
                crawl2(link)
            except:
                pass

from urllib.request import urlopen
import re

def analyze(url):
    """retuns list of http links in url, in absolute format"""
    new_info = []
    
    #print("\n\nVisiting", url) #for testing
    
    #obtain links in the web page
    htmlcontent = urlopen(url).read().decode()
    collector = Collector(url)
    collector.feed(htmlcontent)
    urls = collector.getLinks() #get list of links
    
    #splits list of content into individual words
    info = collector.getData()
    for item in info:
        row_split = re.findall("[a-zA-Z]+", item)
        for thing in row_split:
            new_info.append(thing.lower())
        
    return urls, new_info

#collecting hyperlinks (as absolute URLs) and content

from urllib.parse import urljoin
from html.parser import HTMLParser

class Collector(HTMLParser):
    """collects hyperlink URLs into a list"""
    
    def __init__(self, url):
        """initializes parser, the url, and a list"""
        HTMLParser.__init__(self)
        self.url = url
        self.links = []
        self.data = []
        self.keep = False
        
    def handle_starttag(self, tag, attrs):
        """collects hyperlink URLs in their absolute format"""
        if tag == "a":
            for attr in attrs:
                if attr[0] == "href":
                    #construct absolute URL
                    absolute = urljoin(self.url, attr[1])
                    if absolute[:4] == "http":
                        self.links.append(absolute)
        """determines where to start keeping text data"""
        if tag in ('head', 'title', 'body', 'ul', 'li', 'main', 'article'):
            self.keep = True
    
    def handle_endtag(self, tag):
        """determines where to stop keeping text data"""
        if tag in ('head', 'title', 'body', 'ul', 'li', 'main', 'article'):
            self.keep = False
    
    def getLinks(self):
        """returns hyperlinks URLs in their absolute format"""
        return self.links
    
    def handle_data(self, data):
        """collects the data between headers and tags"""
        if self.keep == True:
            self.data.append(data)
    
    def getData(self):
        """returns meaningful data"""
        return self.data
    
path = input("Please copy and paste a URL to determine the top 25 words on it and its subsequent hyperlinks: ")
crawl2(path)

#converts content list into a dictionary and then "reorders" the dictionary by its frequency 
total_set = set(total)
word_dict = {}
for word in total_set:
    word_dict[word] = total.count(word)
word_sorted_counts = sorted(word_dict, key = word_dict.get, reverse = True)
word_sorted_counts = word_sorted_counts[:25]

#print the frequency of every text data word in original URL's subsequent directory
print("\n{:10} {:5}\n".format("Word", "Frequency"))
for n in word_sorted_counts:
    print("{:10} {:5}".format(n, word_dict[n]))
